narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: We learned about modern cryptography in practice and theory, with a lot of focus on the underlying math.

What people have said in years past holds true: this is a very interesting class, but Professor Fischer is one of the most boring lecturers you will meet. So long as you constantly remind yourself how cool the material is, you will enjoy this class.
Worth taking for the material, which is very interesting. Professor Fischer is not a very interesting lecturer, however, so don't take it if this is a serious problem for you.
I WOULD RECOMMEND THIS CLASS. Despite lectures being a little tedious, I found the concepts fascinating.
